Package: nayoseR
Type: Package
Title: Semantic Name Matching and Deduplication using SBERT
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Takashi Notomi
Maintainer: Takashi Notomi <noutomi0729@gmail.com>
Description: Provides a hybrid R and Python interface for semantic name matching 
    and deduplication tasks. Useful for fuzzy and semantic record linkage in 
    government datasets and business applications. Leverages SBERT (Sentence-BERT) 
    embeddings via the 'reticulate' package to compute cosine similarity between strings, 
    and includes a Shiny interface for human-in-the-loop validation. Supports 
    automatic matching using approved dictionary entries for reproducible name merging.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports: 
    reticulate,
    shiny,
    DT
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
